Key Match Events: Orri Óskarsson scored in the 39' to put Iceland ahead 1-0.
Jon Dagur Thorsteinsson scored in the 58' to make the final score 2-0 in favor of Iceland.
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match was played at Laugardalsvöllur in Reykjavik, Iceland, with an attendance of 4,683.
The referee for the match was Willy Delajod.
Others: Iceland won the match 2-0 against Montenegro, securing 3 points in the UEFA Nations League Group Stage.
